Always refer to @SPEC.md as the single source of truth for this project.

## Development Protocol

- Follow Phase-based development. Do not start Phase N+1 until Phase N acceptance criteria are verified.
- Use "think" blocks before writing complex financial logic or prompt engineering.
- When making decisions not covered by SPEC.md, ask the user before proceeding.

## Code Standards

- Strict TypeScript (`strict: true` in tsconfig). No `any` types except where interfacing with untyped third-party APIs (and annotate those with `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any`).
- All financial arithmetic MUST use `decimal.js`. Never use native `number` for money values.
- All Supabase tables MUST have Row Level Security policies scoped to `auth.uid()`.
- Every page component must be wrapped in an Error Boundary.
- PII must be stripped from any data sent to external APIs (Anthropic, Unstract).

## Data Schema

- All data sources (Flanks, Sharesight, PDF extraction) MUST map to the `UnifiedPortfolio` interface defined in `src/lib/types.ts`.
- Do not add fields to the schema without updating SPEC.md first.

## File Organization

- API routes go in `src/app/api/`.
- Shared types go in `src/lib/types.ts`.
- Supabase client utilities go in `src/lib/supabase/`.
- UI primitives from shadcn/ui go in `src/components/ui/`.
- Feature components go in `src/components/`.

## Testing

- Write unit tests for `decimal.js` helpers and PII masking logic.
- Use mock data from `src/data/mock_bank_data.json` for development and tests.
